Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.54,0:01:54.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.20,0:02:22.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know what the most important\Ntrick to living in this country is, Stevens?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.54,0:02:27.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, sir. I do not...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.54,0:02:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's knowing one's place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.68,0:02:33.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Appropriate behavoir...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.15,0:02:37.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's how order and dignity are maintained.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.99,0:02:47.93,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 6\NThe Visit
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.38,0:03:37.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.48,0:03:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.73,0:04:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma, help me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.97,0:04:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.78,0:04:11.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to make more work for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.25,0:04:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.53,0:04:30.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose I should ask Al\Nto make me a walking stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.00,0:04:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, it really isn't any trouble for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.60,0:04:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.44,0:04:41.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's perfectly fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.14,0:04:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd do anything for you, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.69,0:04:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stevens, my cigars.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.16,0:04:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.37,0:05:13.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey brother, borrow "The Death of\NKing Arthur" for me next time, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.64,0:05:15.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see Beardsley's drawings!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.28,0:05:18.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're not appropriate for you to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.41,0:05:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Beardsley?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.42,0:05:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, he always wears black clothes.\NThey say he looks like the grim reaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.29,0:05:30.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The grim reaper just loves crybabies!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.26,0:05:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.83,0:05:38.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe he'll come visit you tonight, Colin!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.17,0:05:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.44,0:05:47.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.25,0:05:55.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay, there's no such\Nthing as the grim reaper!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.09,0:06:04.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The minute father leaves the room,\Nthe place turns into a zoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.93,0:06:06.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.60,0:06:15.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you're out here again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.84,0:06:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the most pleasant spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.81,0:06:24.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.52,0:06:28.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I envy you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.12,0:06:31.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to rest in this girl's lap?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.99,0:06:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.42,0:06:34.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what is it then?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.56,0:06:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you can act as you please.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.89,0:06:39.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can too, if you wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.27,0:06:49.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Balance, common sense,\Nprinciples and self-control.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.94,0:06:52.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will those virtues make you happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.01,0:06:59.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if Beardsley would\Ndismiss those virtues so easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.35,0:07:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So as heir to the Jones estate,\Nemploying nearly a hundred servants,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.49,0:07:05.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you can't just do as you please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.56,0:07:11.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet... the world can change, if you want it to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.59,0:07:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Young Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.99,0:07:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.69,0:07:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not making any headway on your work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.86,0:07:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... Nice weather, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.00,0:07:54.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's cloudy today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.77,0:07:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It might rain this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.34,0:08:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.81,0:08:08.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We must decide the new\Nfootman's wages. What shall we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.78,0:08:10.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave that up to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.32,0:08:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.46,0:08:16.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is William here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.63,0:08:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe he has gone out, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.26,0:08:22.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To where?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.06,0:08:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, sir. I did not ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.44,0:08:33.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly. I wonder if he plans\Nto attend the ball tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.72,0:08:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stop by again soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.23,0:09:01.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's blatantly using our store\Nas a rendezvous point now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.05,0:09:13.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It certainly is cloudy today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.42,0:09:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.92,0:09:18.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it was so nice this morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.15,0:09:19.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.66,0:09:23.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It made me want to go out somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.93,0:09:26.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.30,0:09:31.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we go somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.40,0:09:35.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the weather's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.67,0:09:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you not want to?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.41,0:09:42.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do want to...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.08,0:09:45.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.12,0:09:54.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Rain...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.06,0:09:55.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.06,0:09:58.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine. I'll hurry home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.46,0:10:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.90,0:10:03.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.50,0:10:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll send you a letter, sometime...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.20,0:10:12.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... Sometime...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.47,0:10:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears he's not coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.87,0:10:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Jones.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.57,0:10:45.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Mrs. Campbell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.84,0:10:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That conspicuous young man\Nis a friend ofWilliam's?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.62,0:11:00.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. William should take a leaf out of\Nhis book when it comes to social skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.86,0:11:05.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me... but where is William?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.53,0:11:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's an unpredictable boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.30,0:11:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please invite him out for a drive\Nwhen the weather clears.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.40,0:11:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll relay the message to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.60,0:11:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.81,0:11:21.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go and get yourself something to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.31,0:11:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eleanor speaks of nothing but\Nyour son William these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.12,0:11:35.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I apologize, he's a boorish child.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.86,0:11:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all! I'd be delighted ifWilliam\Nwould take my daughter's hand in marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.33,0:11:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It would be an honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.54,0:11:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, have you heard?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.27,0:11:52.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I probably haven't, I'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.31,0:11:57.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ladies are much more up-to-date\Nthan myself when it comes to gossip.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.71,0:11:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's about Mrs. Stownar...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.95,0:12:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's apparently had an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.86,0:12:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? To Mrs. Stownar's?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.49,0:12:15.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. I informed her by post\Nthat we'd visit this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.83,0:12:18.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A visit... today?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.53,0:12:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly, William. Why didn't\Nyou tell me about the accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.47,0:12:26.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, l... didn't hear about it directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.61,0:12:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Directly or indirectly, if your mentor\Nis sick, you should call upon her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.71,0:12:34.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.42,0:12:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get ready then!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.25,0:12:41.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-yes, sir...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.46,0:12:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good day!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.63,0:12:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Welcome, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.50,0:12:52.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have any asparagus?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.30,0:12:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do. It just arrived yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.30,0:12:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.41,0:12:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.77,0:13:02.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to boarding school soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.58,0:13:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Going soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.45,0:13:05.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Boarding school?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.38,0:13:08.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.52,0:13:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A state school, miss. Some strange new\Nchanges have been made to the school system.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.36,0:13:17.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm losing my helper to the education board.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.66,0:13:21.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, no one wants to marry\Nan educated woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.30,0:13:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.03,0:13:26.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're in the era of learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.00,0:13:32.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If a girl can recite a piece of poetry,\Nshe might even attract a man of noble birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.07,0:13:36.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hah! Don't go giving her any stupid ideas!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.64,0:13:39.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Having an education doesn't ensure your future.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.65,0:13:42.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.19,0:13:49.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Study hard, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.23,0:13:53.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.56,0:13:57.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please come again!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.53,0:13:58.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please come again!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.70,0:13:59.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.72,0:14:15.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good day!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.82,0:14:18.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A letter, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.22,0:14:19.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.76,0:14:28.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.54,0:14:35.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.97,0:14:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A letter, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.47,0:14:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.54,0:14:43.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a splendid envelope.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.65,0:14:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is a rare honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.92,0:14:49.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.28,0:14:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.03,0:15:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I went to the market today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.13,0:15:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems the price of vegetables\Nhas gone down recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.67,0:15:06.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that so...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.17,0:15:12.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been making puddings\Nfor dinner so often lately...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.24,0:15:13.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...so I bought some asparagus today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.67,0:15:14.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.91,0:15:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Jones and his son are calling in to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.95,0:15:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no need for you to come...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.46,0:15:33.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been meaning to call\Nupon her anyway. It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.26,0:15:36.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be enough if I just visit by myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.26,0:15:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,William!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.23,0:15:41.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need to learn a bit more about manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.20,0:15:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You never even visited your\Ngoverness until I told you to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.44,0:15:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am grateful for that advice at least.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.20,0:16:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It appears they have arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.99,0:16:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Jones.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.56,0:16:43.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've been waiting for you, sir. Right this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.38,0:17:02.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been too long!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.45,0:17:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't expect you come all this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.12,0:17:09.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me for not standing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.99,0:17:12.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all, Mrs. Stownar.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.87,0:17:24.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.51,0:17:28.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,William.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.51,0:17:29.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Er... yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.48,0:17:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time, Mr. Jones.\NYou haven't changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.25,0:17:40.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You look surprisingly well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.22,0:17:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I merely twisted my leg. It's nothing serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.39,0:17:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,William said nothing about it.\NI apologize for not visiting sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.77,0:17:53.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, think nothing of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.10,0:17:57.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid my son has no manners.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.44,0:18:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He must have been so troublesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.01,0:18:07.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, not at all. He was a fine student.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.32,0:18:11.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He just suffered from a\Nslight lack of concentration.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.09,0:18:19.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certainly glad to hear that, but William\Ncan be complacent. It's a flaw in his character.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.60,0:18:27.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I keep cautioning him about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.27,0:18:31.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but unfortunately he lacks\Na sense of self-awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.34,0:18:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't blame him. He's of a certain age.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.21,0:18:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's about time for William to take...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.50,0:19:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.67,0:19:03.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The scones.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.30,0:19:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.74,0:19:16.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's about time for William to\Ntake charge of the family business.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.72,0:19:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although I am very healthy at present,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.92,0:19:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I may meet with an accident\Nlike yours at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.36,0:19:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.06,0:19:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.20,0:19:30.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I tried to be careful...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.23,0:19:36.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So when I consider what could happen,\Nit makes me very uneasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.84,0:19:40.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think William will mature\Nif he takes on some responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.38,0:19:44.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm also arranging a match for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.95,0:19:52.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a certain lady who would like William\Nto take her daughter's hand in marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.25,0:19:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute! What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.69,0:19:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the first I've heard of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.29,0:20:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. These matters have to be\Ndiscussed by the parents first.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.23,0:20:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.63,0:20:06.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mrs. Campbell's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.37,0:20:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.74,0:20:10.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't 50 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.21,0:20:13.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just because the parents have\Nmade up their minds about marriage,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.01,0:20:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it doesn't mean the children\Nmust comply with their wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.54,0:20:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there someone you have your heart set upon?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.55,0:20:21.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha-?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.55,0:20:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well? Is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.59,0:20:29.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you see...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.32,0:20:33.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I assume she is a lady worthy\Nof joining the Jones family.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.17,0:20:47.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.08,0:20:50.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.15,0:20:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your personal feelings are important, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.19,0:21:02.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you must marry someone\Nfrom the same country.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.72,0:21:05.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's not a foreigner, father.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.79,0:21:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,England is one nation, but there\Nare two countries within it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.56,0:21:13.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the aristocracy\Nand the commoners.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.74,0:21:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Although these two countries share\Nthe same language, they are divided.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.75,0:21:27.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Jones!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.55,0:21:33.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive me... This is not a subject\Nwe should be discussing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.72,0:21:36.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'd best be on our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.34,0:21:56.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,William!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.47,0:24:09.00,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Episode:\NCrystal Palace
